title: H.S. football: Coming attractions
text:
October 19, 2015 Last updated: Monday, October 19, 2015, 1:20 AM The Record Print 
Coming attractions 
No. 3 Paramus Catholic (3-3) at IMG Academy (6-0), Friday, 7 p.m.: The Paladins will attempt to continue their turnaround in Bradenton, Fla. IMG is ranked No. 8 in USA Today’s Super 25 national poll. 
No. 14 Lakeland (4-2) at No. 7 Wayne Valley (6-0), Friday, 7 p.m.: The Lancers will try to ruin the Indians’ perfect season. 
No. 9 Hackensack (3-2) at No. 10 Ridgewood (5-1), Friday, 7 p.m.: The visiting Comets can climb in the North 1, Group 5 power-point standings by winning this game. 
No. 15 Garfield (5-1) at No. 11 Rutherford (6-0), Friday, 7 p.m.: First place in the NJIC Colonial Division is at stake in this one. 
No. 4 Don Bosco (4-2) at Bishop Gorman (8-0), Friday, 10 p.m.: The Ironmen will face a challenge in Las Vegas, where they’ll encounter a squad ranked No. 1 in the nation by USA Today. 
No. 2 St. Joseph (5-2) at No. 1 Bergen Catholic (4-2), Saturday, 1 p.m.: The Green Knights and Crusaders will play for the top spot in the Big North United Division and plenty of Non-Public, Group 4 power points. 
— Mark J. Czerwinski and Keith Idec © 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
